<task id="036" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Deploy EmailComposer Code Page to dev as `sprk_emailcomposer` web resource</title>
    <phase>Wave 2 — EmailComposer Code Page + Entry Surfaces</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>034</dependencies>
    <blocks>037, 038, 040, 041, 042, 043, 044, 045</blocks>
    <tags>deploy, code-page, dataverse</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Deploy step using the canonical `code-page-deploy` skill; verifies the artifact lands in Dataverse + smoke-tested via direct URL</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Hub task — entry surfaces (037, 038, 040) and UI tests (041–045) all depend on a deployed Code Page</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>FR-18</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Deploy the EmailComposer Code Page to the dev environment as Dataverse web resource `sprk_emailcomposer` using the `code-page-deploy` skill. After deploy, verify:
    1. Direct URL access: open `https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer?data=...` (or Dataverse-equivalent) and confirm the Code Page loads
    2. Auth bootstrap succeeds without a popup (silent acquisition path)
    3. All 5 modes (compose/view/reply/forward/draft) render appropriate UI given test URL params
    4. No console errors on cold load
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke deployment engineer. Familiar with the `code-page-deploy` skill conventions, Dataverse web resource lifecycle (create/update), and PAC CLI / solution publish flow.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_emailcomposer` web resource exists in the dev Dataverse environment, references the latest `build-webresource.ps1` output, and is publicly accessible at its web resource URL. Smoke-test report confirms auth and 5 modes work.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-18, the Code Page deploys as the `sprk_emailcomposer` web resource and serves as the canonical surface for the 3 entry points (ribbon, Form Component Control, embeddable). This task is the gate before tasks 037/038/040/041–045 can land.

      The `code-page-deploy` skill is the canonical deployer for this pattern (used by DocumentRelationshipViewer and other Code Pages). Invoke it; do not hand-roll a deploy script.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/EmailComposer/dist/sprk_emailcomposer.html (deploy artifact from task 034)</file>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/EmailComposer/build-webresource.ps1 (the deploy script)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="code-page-deploy skill">Use the canonical skill — do not introduce a bespoke deploy script</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-026">Code Page deploys as full-page custom page web resource</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Auth bootstrap is `@spaarke/auth` v2 — verify silent acquisition post-deploy</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Web resource name: `sprk_emailcomposer` (type: Web Page (HTML))</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Dev environment only — do not deploy to prod from this task</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No `.claude/` writes in this Wave 2 task</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/code-page-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-026-full-page-custom-page-standard.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/ENVIRONMENT-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Code Page deploy via skill" location=".claude/skills/code-page-deploy/SKILL.md">
        Invoke the skill; it handles build → upload → publish → verification cycle.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Confirm task 034 output: `dist/sprk_emailcomposer.html` exists and is the latest build.</step>
    <step order="2">Invoke the `code-page-deploy` skill with target = dev environment, web resource name = `sprk_emailcomposer`, source = build output path.</step>
    <step order="3">Wait for skill to complete: build → upload → publish customizations.</step>
    <step order="4">Verify deploy: query Dataverse via PAC CLI or Web API to confirm `sprk_emailcomposer` exists, latest published, type = Web Page (HTML).</step>
    <step order="5">Smoke test 1 (auth): open `https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer` directly in a browser logged in as a Spaarke user. Confirm:
      - Code Page loads (HTML mounts)
      - No popup for auth
      - DevTools Network shows `/token` calls succeed silently
      - DevTools Console: zero errors
    </step>
    <step order="6">Smoke test 2 (modes): open the Code Page with each of the 5 mode URLs:
      - `?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22compose%22%7D` → empty compose form
      - `?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22view%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-record-guid}%22%7D` → view UI
      - `?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22reply%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-record-guid}%22%7D` → reply UI
      - `?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22forward%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-record-guid}%22%7D` → forward UI
      - `?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22draft%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-draft-guid}%22%7D` → draft UI
      Confirm each mode renders the appropriate composer state.
    </step>
    <step order="7">Document smoke-test results in `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/036-deploy-smoketest.md` (URL, screenshots if available, observations per mode).</step>
    <step order="8">If any mode fails smoke test, file a defect note and BLOCK on it before marking task complete (the failure likely indicates a Wave 1 or Wave 2 prior-task regression).</step>
    <step order="9">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 036 ✅ completed; reference smoke-test note.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed; advance to next pending task (037 or parallel-group H starts).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="code-page-deploy">Invoke skill</tool>
    <tool name="bash">PAC CLI verification + smoke-test browser checks via Chrome integration if available</tool>
    <tool name="write">Smoke-test note</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="deploy">Dataverse `sprk_emailcomposer` web resource (CREATED/UPDATED in dev)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/036-deploy-smoketest.md (NEW — smoke test results)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`sprk_emailcomposer` web resource exists in dev Dataverse, published, type = Web Page (HTML).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Direct URL access loads the Code Page in a browser without errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Auth bootstrap succeeds silently (no popup in steady state).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 5 modes render their respective UI given correct URL params.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">DevTools Console shows zero errors on cold load.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Smoke-test note documents the results.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No `.claude/` files modified in this task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The `code-page-deploy` skill handles bumping the version + publishing customizations. If invocation order matters (build first, then upload), follow the skill's protocol exactly.

    Smoke-test record GUIDs: pick existing `sprk_communication` records from dev (one Draft, one Sent) for view/reply/forward/draft mode tests. If no records exist, create one via the standard form first (before Form Component Control swap in task 038).

    Empirical (CLAUDE.md §3): this task does not write to `.claude/`, so it's sub-agent-safe; the deploy is the only Dataverse mutation in Wave 2 to this point.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>
      Load all `<knowledge><files>` before starting. Apply STANDARD rigor per `<rigor-hint>`. Quality gates at Step 9.5 are SKIPPED for STANDARD rigor. Invoke `code-page-deploy` skill for the deploy mechanics.
    </protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
